<article class="project">
	<h2>HTML5 Picross</h2>
	<h3>Logic based puzzle game.</h2>
	<p>Final project during the Web Development Immersive at General Assembly.  Open-ended project to use technologies learned during the course.</p>

	<h4>Features</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>Users use the provided numbers to decypher which cells in the grid are filled.</li>
		<li>Users can flag cells to assist in decyphering the board.</li>
		<li>A completely puzzle board will then form a picture.</li>
		<li>Logic and features similar to Sudoku and Minesweeper.</li>
	</ul>

	<h4>Technical Features</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>Puzzle board built in served on the backend.</li>
		<li>JavaScript retrieves the puzzle key via AJAX request, then monitors the gameboard interactions and compares them against the puzzle key. </li>
		<li>Ruby on Rails, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, jQuery, Underscore.js, AJAX.</li>
	</ul>
	
