<article class="project">
	<h2>AnyQuestions</h2>
	<h3>Classroom tool for asking questions.</h2>
	<p>Real-time tool for making sure the most common questions are answered while letting the instructor control the flow of the lesson.</p>

	<h4>Features</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>Students ask questions which are then updated for all students in realtime.</li>
		<li>Other students can upvote any questions that they also have.</li>
		<li>The question list will resort based on the most common questions.</li>
		<li>Instructor can monitor the question list and decide if a question needs to be answered before continuing on, or if they should come back to the question at a later time.</li>
		<li>Once a question has been answered it can be dismissed by the instructor.</li>
	</ul>

	<h4>Technical Features</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>Single page application updated in real time via AJAX requests.</li>
		<li>Custom JavaScript MVC adds and removes questions, tracks questions' upvotes, and maintains proper sorting of questions in real time.</li>
		<li>Ruby on Rails, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, custom JavaScript MVC, jQuery, Underscore.js, AJAX.</li>
	</ul>
	
